onChange.script:
from threading import Timer
	
	if self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.start == self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.end:
		# no time range selected, hide chart
		self.custom.analysis.dataLoading = True
		self.custom.analysis.placeholderText = "No time range selected"
	else:
		# time range selected, disable xtrace and update data
		self.custom.analysis.xtrace = False
		
		def async():
			# update range
			self.custom.rangeSelector.zeroedRange ={
				'min': (system.date.toMillis(self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.start) - self.custom.parsedData.startTimeOffset) / 1000.0,
				'max': (system.date.toMillis(self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.end) - self.custom.parsedData.startTimeOffset) / 1000.0,
				'useStrict': True
			}
			
			# configure series based on selected channels
			series = []
			colorIndex = 0
			for i in self.custom.options.channels.instances:
				if i['value']:
					template = system.util.jsonDecode(system.util.jsonEncode(self.custom.analysis.seriesTemplate))
					template['visible'] = True
					template['data']['y'] = i['channel']
					template['name'] = i['text']
					template['label']['text'] = i['text']
					template['line']['appearance']['stroke']['color'] = self.custom.colors[colorIndex%len(self.custom.colors)]
					series.append(template)
					colorIndex+=1
			
			# update data based on selected channels and time
			# filter columns
			dataset = system.util.getGlobals()['exchange']['comtrade'][self.session.props.id][self.page.props.pageId]['highRes']
			filteredColumns = system.dataset.filterColumns(
				dataset
				, ['zeroedSeconds'] + [i['channel'] for i in self.custom.options.channels.instances if i['value']]
			)
			
			# filter rows
			deleteRows = [i for i in xrange(dataset.getRowCount()) 
				if dataset.getValueAt(i,'time') > self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.end
				or dataset.getValueAt(i,'time') < self.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange.start
			]
			filteredDataset = system.dataset.deleteRows(filteredColumns, deleteRows)

			# send one object			
			self.custom.analysis = {
				"dataLoading": False,
				"xtrace": False,
				"dataset": filteredDataset,
				"placeholderText": "No time range selected",
				"series": series,
				"seriesTemplate": self.custom.analysis.seriesTemplate,
				"title": self.custom.analysis.title
			}
			
		Timer(0.02, async).start()

transforms.code:
output = []
	isSelected = True
	for chType in ['A', 'D']:
		for i, ch in enumerate(value.data[chType]):
			template = system.util.jsonDecode(system.util.jsonEncode(self.custom.options.channels.instanceTemplate))
			template['value'] = isSelected
			isSelected = False
			template['channel'] = '%s%s' % (chType, i+1)
			template['text'] = '%s - %s' % (template['channel'], ch['ch_id'])
			template['tooltip'] = str(ch).replace(',',',\n')
			template['generated'] = system.date.now()
			output.append(template)
	return output

system.perspective.print('channels changed, recalculating range selector data')
	return system.dataset.filterColumns(
		system.util.getGlobals()['exchange']['comtrade'][self.session.props.id][self.page.props.pageId]['lowRes']
		, ['time'] + [i['channel'] for i in value if i['value']])

config.script:
self.view.custom.rangeSelector.data = None
	self.view.custom.rangeSelector.placeholderText = "Parsing file, please wait"
	def async():
		now = system.date.now()
		self.view.custom.analysis.dataset = None
		self.view.custom.analysis.dataLoading = True
		self.view.custom.rangeSelector.selectedRange = {
			"end": now,
			"start": now
		}
		self.view.custom.parsedData = exchange.comtrade.utils.parse(
			self.view.custom.tree.selectionData[0].value.fullPath
			,self.session.props.id
			,self.page.props.pageId
			,dateFormat = self.view.custom.options.dateFormat
		)
	system.util.invokeAsynchronous(async)

path = exchange.comtrade.utils.folderUpload()
	if not system.file.fileExists(path):
		import os
		os.makedirs(path)
	filename = path + event.file.name
	event.file.copyTo(filename)
	self.view.custom.tree.items = exchange.comtrade.utils.localTree()

# get all .cfg .dat .inf files and compress them into a zip
	import os
	import zipfile
	
	filePath = self.view.custom.tree.selectionData[0].value.fullPath

	# determine file properties
	fileNoExt, fileExt = os.path.splitext(filePath)
	if fileExt == '':
		# exit script if folder is selected
		return
	fileDir, fileName = os.path.split(filePath)
	fileNameNoExt = fileName.replace(fileExt, '')
	
	# compiling a list of files to zip
	filesToZip = [filePath]
	fileNames = [fileName]
	for ft in ['.cfg', '.dat', '.inf']:
		newPath = '%s%s'%(fileNoExt,ft)
		if system.file.fileExists(newPath) and newPath not in filesToZip:
			filesToZip.append(newPath)
			fileNames.append('%s%s'%(fileNameNoExt, ft))
	
	# create zip file
	tempZip = system.file.getTempFile('zip')
	with zipfile.ZipFile(tempZip, 'w') as myzip:
	    for fl, nm in zip(filesToZip, fileNames):
	        myzip.write(fl,nm)

	# download file
	filename = '%s.zip'%(fileNameNoExt)
	data = system.file.readFileAsBytes(tempZip)
	system.perspective.download(filename, data)
	
	# delete temp file
	os.remove(tempZip)

system.util.execute([exchange.comtrade.utils.sftpScript()])
	from threading import Timer
	def doLater():
		self.view.custom.tree.items = exchange.comtrade.utils.localTree()
	Timer(0.5, doLater).start()
